HEADWORD: Counteract
<hw>Coun`ter*act"</hw> <pr>(koun`t?r-?kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Counteracted</conjf>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Counteracting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To act
in opposition to; to hinder, defeat, or frustrate, by contrary agency or
influence; <as>as, to <ex>counteract</ex> the effect of medicines; to
<ex>counteract</ex> good advice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counteraction</ent>⟦br⟧
